•	Epistemological humility: Recognition that human knowledge is infinitesimally small compared to the vastness of the unknown
•	Lifelong learning: The acknowledgment that learning never ends; there's always more to discover
•	Cosmic perspective: Placing individual achievement in context of universal knowledge
•	Anti-arrogance: A reminder against intellectual pride or the illusion of complete knowledge
•	Curiosity cultivation: Inspiring wonder and continued pursuit of wisdom
•	The paradox of wisdom: True wisdom lies in knowing how little we know (Socratic wisdom)
